<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-19T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-19T14:00:00-05:00" n="459" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">438.00/167: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-19T14:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 19,
                                        1922—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 23—10:30
                                    a.m.]<note n="92" xml:id="d459fn92">Text printed from corrected
                                    copy received Oct. 24, 1922.</note></dateline></opener>
                        <p>127. President Borno has informed me that he intends Abel N. Léger as
                            Haitian member of Claims Commission. Mr. Léger is son of former Haitian
                            Minister to the United States and a lawyer of prominence …</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>